  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Federal contract obligations in Wyoming totaled $508M in FY2026 to date, with an awardCount of 1,687 and an averageAwardSize of $301K. Obligations are up 2.3% year over year. Historical annual totals show variation: FY21 was $390M, FY22 was $559M, FY23 was $470M, FY24 was $532M, and FY25 was $497M. The Department of the Interior is the dominant buyer at $308M in FY2026 to date, followed by the Department of Defense at $74.1M and the Department of Veterans Affairs at $41.7M. Construction-related industries account for the largest shares of spending: Water and Sewer Line and Related Structures Construction received $246M, Highway, Street, and Bridge Construction received $62.2M, and Commercial and Institutional Building Construction received $52.8M. Major vendors in FY2026 to date include RECORD STEEL AND CONSTRUCTION, INC. at $129M and G.S.E. CONSTRUCTION COMPANY, INC. at $109M, with other top contractors such as THE ARMORED GROUP LLC at $26.4M and AECOM + TETRA TECH JOINT VENTURE at $22.7M.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies drive federal contracting in Wyoming?",
        "body": "The Department of the Interior leads Wyoming obligations with $308M in FY2026 to date. The Department of Defense follows with $74.1M and the Department of Veterans Affairs with $41.7M. Several civilian agencies also contribute, including the Department of Transportation at $37.6M and the General Services Administration at $26.7M."
      },
      {
        "heading": "What industries and vendors capture the most obligations?",
        "body": "Construction and infrastructure industries dominate: Water and Sewer Line and Related Structures Construction accounts for $246M, while Highway, Street, and Bridge Construction accounts for $62.2M and Commercial and Institutional Building Construction accounts for $52.8M. RECORD STEEL AND CONSTRUCTION, INC. and G.S.E. CONSTRUCTION COMPANY, INC. are the largest vendors at $129M and $109M respectively, followed by THE ARMORED GROUP LLC at $26.4M and AECOM + TETRA TECH JOINT VENTURE at $22.7M."
      }
    ]
  },
